---
/**
 * transactions-isolation-fundamentals · Figure 6 — Level 9, the decision tree
 * mapping the SHAPE of a write (one row / cross-row / cross-service) to its fix.
 *
 * Copied VERBATIM from
 * docs/transactions-isolation/transactions-isolation-fundamentals.html (figure +
 * svg + figcaption). Lives as an .astro component, NOT inline in the MDX,
 * because MDX's JSX parser is unreliable with raw inline SVG that uses
 * kebab-case attrs.
 *
 * The source page defines the arrowhead markers once in a top-of-body
 * <svg defs> (#arw grey, #arwA red, #arwG green). This figure references #arw,
 * so it is inlined here in a local <defs> (verbatim from that defs block) so the
 * marker-end="url(#…)" references resolve standalone.
 */
---

<figure>
    <svg
        viewBox="0 0 600 210"
        role="img"
        aria-label="A decision tree mapping the shape of a write to its fix: single row, cross-row invariant, or cross-service workflow"
    >
        <defs>
            <marker
                id="arw"
                viewBox="0 0 10 10"
                refX="8.5"
                refY="5"
                markerWidth="7"
                markerHeight="7"
                orient="auto-start-reverse"
                ><path d="M0,0 L10,5 L0,10 z" fill="#6b675f"></path></marker
            >
        </defs>
        <g font-family="ui-sans-serif,system-ui,sans-serif">
            <rect
                x="210"
                y="10"
                width="180"
                height="34"
                rx="9"
                fill="#f1eee2"
                stroke="#7a1f12"
                stroke-width="1.5"></rect>
            <text
                x="300"
                y="26"
                text-anchor="middle"
                font-size="10.5"
                font-weight="700"
                fill="#7a1f12">does this read feed a write?</text
            >
            <text x="300" y="38" text-anchor="middle" font-size="8.5" fill="#6b675f"
                >what invariant must hold after commit?</text
            >
            <!-- three branches -->
            <line x1="250" y1="44" x2="110" y2="80" stroke="#6b675f" marker-end="url(#arw)"></line>
            <line x1="300" y1="44" x2="300" y2="80" stroke="#6b675f" marker-end="url(#arw)"></line>
            <line x1="350" y1="44" x2="490" y2="80" stroke="#6b675f" marker-end="url(#arw)"></line>
            <g>
                <rect x="20" y="82" width="170" height="40" rx="8" fill="#fff" stroke="#d8d4c8"
                ></rect>
                <text
                    x="105"
                    y="98"
                    text-anchor="middle"
                    font-size="9.5"
                    font-weight="700"
                    fill="#111110">ONE row</text
                >
                <text x="105" y="112" text-anchor="middle" font-size="8.5" fill="#6b675f"
                    >counter / balance</text
                >
            </g>
            <g>
                <rect x="215" y="82" width="170" height="40" rx="8" fill="#fff" stroke="#d8d4c8"
                ></rect>
                <text
                    x="300"
                    y="98"
                    text-anchor="middle"
                    font-size="9.5"
                    font-weight="700"
                    fill="#111110">CROSS-ROW invariant</text
                >
                <text x="300" y="112" text-anchor="middle" font-size="8.5" fill="#6b675f"
                    >≥1 doctor; no double-book</text
                >
            </g>
            <g>
                <rect x="410" y="82" width="170" height="40" rx="8" fill="#fff" stroke="#d8d4c8"
                ></rect>
                <text
                    x="495"
                    y="98"
                    text-anchor="middle"
                    font-size="9.5"
                    font-weight="700"
                    fill="#111110">CROSS-SERVICE</text
                >
                <text x="495" y="112" text-anchor="middle" font-size="8.5" fill="#6b675f"
                    >reserve→charge→ticket</text
                >
            </g>
            <line x1="105" y1="122" x2="105" y2="150" stroke="#6b675f" marker-end="url(#arw)"
            ></line>
            <line x1="300" y1="122" x2="300" y2="150" stroke="#6b675f" marker-end="url(#arw)"
            ></line>
            <line x1="495" y1="122" x2="495" y2="150" stroke="#6b675f" marker-end="url(#arw)"
            ></line>
            <g>
                <rect x="20" y="152" width="170" height="44" rx="8" fill="#eef5ee" stroke="#2f5d3a"
                ></rect>
                <text
                    x="105"
                    y="170"
                    text-anchor="middle"
                    font-size="9.5"
                    font-weight="700"
                    fill="#2f5d3a">atomic write /</text
                >
                <text
                    x="105"
                    y="184"
                    text-anchor="middle"
                    font-size="9.5"
                    font-weight="700"
                    fill="#2f5d3a">FOR UPDATE</text
                >
            </g>
            <g>
                <rect x="215" y="152" width="170" height="44" rx="8" fill="#eef5ee" stroke="#2f5d3a"
                ></rect>
                <text
                    x="300"
                    y="170"
                    text-anchor="middle"
                    font-size="9.5"
                    font-weight="700"
                    fill="#2f5d3a">Serializable (SSI) /</text
                >
                <text
                    x="300"
                    y="184"
                    text-anchor="middle"
                    font-size="9.5"
                    font-weight="700"
                    fill="#2f5d3a">materialized lock row</text
                >
            </g>
            <g>
                <rect x="410" y="152" width="170" height="44" rx="8" fill="#eef5ee" stroke="#2f5d3a"
                ></rect>
                <text
                    x="495"
                    y="170"
                    text-anchor="middle"
                    font-size="9.5"
                    font-weight="700"
                    fill="#2f5d3a">saga + idempotency</text
                >
                <text
                    x="495"
                    y="184"
                    text-anchor="middle"
                    font-size="9.5"
                    font-weight="700"
                    fill="#2f5d3a">(no level reaches here)</text
                >
            </g>
        </g>
    </svg>
    <figcaption>
        Three shapes, three fixes. The senior instinct in one line: lock the row you can name,
        serialize the conflict you can't, make idempotent everything that crosses a wire.
    </figcaption>
</figure>
